// Track W (techdesign-03-floor-wasm.md §5): time/random SHAPE pins for the
// wasm floor's now_ms/now_ns/random imports — property checks only, no golden
// values (the sys_natives.lev convention for nondeterminism), so the same
// file is byte-identical on every lane that runs it (house rule, doc 00 §6:
// portable pins simply gain the wasm lane). The environment-dependent
// natives sys_natives.lev also exercises (env/tty/fs) are wasm-gated and
// stay out of this file on purpose.

// monotonic: a later read never precedes an earlier one.
int a = std::sysMonotonic();
int b = std::sysMonotonic();
console.writeln((b >= a).toString());

// wall clock: epoch ms, and the clock is actually set (any instant this
// pin can run at is after 2020-01-01; Date.now() on the wasm host,
// CLOCK_REALTIME elsewhere).
console.writeln((std::sysNow() > 1577836800000).toString());

// random: requested length is honoured; n<=0 is the empty string.
console.writeln(std::sysRandom(0).length().toString());
console.writeln(std::sysRandom(24).length().toString());
